  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Sustainable Infrastructure Programme Latin America (SIP-LA) is a &#xA3;177.5m bilateral programme funded by UK International Climate Finance (ICF) and delivered by the Inter-American Development Bank (IDB). SIP-LA supports partner countries to achieve their emission reduction commitments by mobilising private investment into low-carbon infrastructure. The programme provides public sector technical assistance alongside private sector technical assistance and blended finance investments. It works with four partner countries: Brazil, Colombia, Mexico, and Peru.</narrative>
  </description>
